# Project Telos Six-Month Public-Interest Budget

Date: 2026-06-29

Project Telos is a public, local-first tool line for making AI-assisted work checkable instead of merely convincing. The current flagships are gather for source receipts, index for rerunnable workspace maps, forum for routing ledgers, crucible for measured judgment and refinement, and telos for shared human/model work surfaces.

This budget supports a six-month public validation cycle for agent-work receipts, local-first workflow demos, and community testing across AI safety, digital security, open-source maintenance, research, and creative/scientific workflows.

